==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monerula
<hw>Mo*ner"u*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., dim. of
<ets>moner</ets>. See <er>Monera</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A
germ in that stage of development in which its form is simply that of a
non-nucleated mass of protoplasm. It precedes the one-celled germ. So
called from its likeness to a moner.</def>
<rj><au>Haeckel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monesia</ent>⟦br⟧
